President Obama has signed an Executive Order creating a Presidential Emergency Board to investigate and make recommendations for the settlement of disputes between the New Jersey Transit Rail and its employees. The board will report its findings and recommendations to the President within 30 days. President Obama has appointed three members to the board: Elizabeth C. Wesman as Chair, Barbara Deinhardt as a member, and Ann Kenis as a member. These individuals have experience in labor and employment arbitration and mediation in various industries. The President emphasized the importance of resolving the labor-management disputes in order to ensure the smooth operation of the transit rail system, which is vital to the nation's economy.